n prove puzzling to the non-specialist. The biographical chapter not only provides relevant factual information but also draws attention to significant patterns in Rameau's life and work. This book counters the widespread perception of the composer as a dry, irascible, unsociable individual, revealing him in a far more sympathetic light by giving due weight to hitherto little-known information. GRAHAM SADLER is Professor Emeritus at the University of Hull, Research Professor at Birmingham Conservatoire and Research Fellow at the University of Oxford. He is known internationally as an authority on French music of the seventeenth and eighteenth centuries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aComposerszFrancevBiography. 4aEighteenth Century Studies. 4aMusic. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Classical.2bisacsh  aFrance.  aFrench music.  aJean-Philippe Rameau.  aacademia.  abiography.  acomposer.  aeighteenth century.  ahistory of music.  amemoir.  amusic theory.  amusicology.  aprimary source.  aresearch.  aseventeenth century.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2014z978311143136940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978178204363840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782043638423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782043638/original  a978-3-11-143136-9  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2014b2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles